post_text:
We are pleased to announce that effective immediately, NVUSD is offering free meals to all children thanks to a new national program that funds free meals to all children into the fall months.

Parents can pick up curbside meals at the regular Monday/Thursday schedule for any child in the household who is 18 years or younger.

ALSO! We recently received a generous cheese donation from Cypress Grove! Every family who picks up a meal on Thursday, September 10 will receive a 1 pound wheel of Truffle Tremor Mini cheese. YUM!

URGENT: Zoom outage -- instructions for today's classes

Dear NVUSD Families, Students and Staff,

The Zoom platform is currently experiencing a system-wide outage for most of its customers globally. According to news reports, there is no expected time of resolution. This outage will affect today’s school schedule and synchronous online teaching will be suspended until Zoom is operational again.

Teachers will be posting assignments on Google classroom and SeeSaw and we ask that students check in each hour or class period to determine if they are able to access Zoom. The district will send another message once we are assured Zoom is online and operational.

Thank you for your patience.

post_text:
If you have a minute today between 11 and noon, drop by Napa High for lunch. Not only will you get FREE food for your family for three days and fresh tomatoes and strawberries, you might get the chance to say, “Goodbye and Thank you!” to Brandy Dreibelbis.
Brandy has served as NVUSD’s Nutrition Director for the last three years. During that time she has led the transformation of the NVUSD food program from processed, heat-and-serve offerings to healthy, tasty, from-scratch meals.
Brandy leaves NVUSD this week. She will be joining the Chef Ann Foundation’s team in their mission to help school communities across the nation create healthier food. We were fortunate to have had Brandy for head chef as our new program (NOSH - Napa’s Operative for School Food Health) was developed and established. Hers will be big mitts to fill, but thanks to her we have all the ingredients to keep this award-winning program cooking!
Thank you Brandy!

Napa County Office of Education
May 23 at 12:00 AM ·

Napa County Office of Education & Napa Valley Unified School District collaborated to purchase and assemble "Care Kits" for 275 students currently experiencing homelessness. Although these families are being contacted by the NVUSD social workers and NCOE to ensure they feel supported and have what they need for distance learning during shelter in place, the care kit will hopefully provide a little comfort to those who have this additional hardship. NCOE Prevention Health and Wellness.

post_text: Teaching is an act of love at any time, but even more so now when we are apart. Earlier this week we asked parents to send us pictures and videos of their students showing their appreciation for teachers. In less than 24 hours our inbox was overflowing with love and support! We had too many submissions to include them all, but we used quite a few to make this video. We will continue to share more on our Facebook page and will also forward individual messages to teachers to make sure they see them. Thank you so much for all the creative and heartfelt submissions!

Have you responded to the 2020 Census yet? If not, or if you aren't sure, do it now! Go to https://2020census.gov/
Help us make sure EVERY child is counted in the 2020 Census. This count impacts the federal funds that communities receive for special education, classroom technology, teacher training, after-school programs, school lunch assistance, and more.
When responding to the Census, remember to include ALL people living in your home, including babies a.k.a. future students!
Napa County Library Napa County Office of Education Boys & Girls Clubs of Napa Valley Alta Heights Elementary School Willow Elementary Irene M. Snow Elementary School Shearer Elementary School American Canyon Middle School Napa Valley Language Academy Northwood Elementary School West Park Elementary Pueblo Vista

We want to hear from you!
NVUSD is seeking community input on the development of new trustee area boundaries as we continue the districting process.
Draft maps create by our independent demographers based on the feedback and input we received from community members over the last several weeks are now available for public viewing.
We invite you to view these draft maps (link below) and provide any feedback you have either during our virtual Board of Education Public Hearing on April 23 (link below), or by emailing comments to districting@nvusd.org.
Thank you!
Maps: nvusd.k12.ca.us/districting
Hearing: nvusd.org/board

Our teachers and staff have been working so hard to help our children and us, as parents, succeed with Distance Learning. Hopefully this brings a little smile to their faces before the challenging week ahead. Just a reminder that we see all of your hard work, and know that each and every one of you are doing the best you can during this challenging time!! We are all so proud to be apart of the Northwood Community!

With so much gratitude,
The Northwood Eagles & Their Parents

Nuestros maestros y personal han estado trabajando muy duro para ayudar a nuestros hijos y a nosotros, como padres, a tener éxito con la educación a distancia. Esperamos que esto les traiga una pequeña sonrisa antes de la semana desafiante que se avecina. ¡Solo un recordatorio de que vemos todo su arduo trabajo y sabemos que todos y cada uno de ustedes están haciendo lo mejor que pueden durante este momento desafiante! ¡Estamos muy orgullosos de ser parte de la comunidad de Northwood!

Con tanta gratitud,
Las aguilas de Northwood y sus padres

post_text:
New 2-day food distribution schedule begins tomorrow, April 6

Based on feedback, we are implementing a new food distribution schedule starting on Monday, April 6th. We will distribute food twice a week on Mondays and Thursdays from 11:00 am - 12:00.

Additional meals will be provided on Mondays and Thursdays to cover the weekdays that our distribution sites will not be open.

Locations are as follows:
Napa High School - 2475 Jefferson Street, Napa
In the parking lot at the front of the school office.

Shearer Elementary School - 1590 Elm St, Napa
At the curb on Elm street in front of the school.

Redwood Middle School - 3600 Oxford St, Napa
In the bus/student dropoff area at the front of the school

Napa Valley Language Academy (NVLA) - 2700 Kilburn Ave., Napa

American Canyon Middle School - 300 Benton Way, American Canyon
In the drop off/pick up driveway in front of the school office.

Vintage HS alum Maria Alvarez Pineda is ready to tackle Global Public Health challenges!
Dominican is one of only a handful of universities offering an undergraduate degree in Global Public Health. Dr. Bayles is at the forefront of the emerging academic discipline of planetary health, which examines how environmental change impacts the spread of disease, including COVID-19 coronavirus.

Dr. Bayles is an epidemiologist. Maria now aspires to be one, too. Go Maria!!!

Dr. Bayles is at the forefront of the emerging academic discipline of planetary health, which examines how environmental change impacts the spread of disease, including COVID-19 coronavirus.

Dr. Bayles is an epidemiologist. Maria now aspires to be one, too. Go Maria!!!

DOMINICAN.EDU
Picture Perfect Progression To Public Health

March is Women's History Month and we have a lot of history to celebrate and remember.
This year marks the 100th anniversary of the passage of the 19th Amendment which granted women throughout the United State the right to vote.
The film Iron-Jawed Angels dramatizes the groundbreaking work of suffragists Alice Paul and Lucy Burns which revolutionized the American feminist movement in the 1910s.
This special, free screening is co-hosted by the Napa County Library and the League of Women Voters Napa County.
[some material may be deemed inappropriate for children, parental discretion advised]

Each year Napa County Reads selects a book to read and invites the author to visit Napa. Teachers, students and the community are encouraged to read the book together as a community-wide “Book Club” before the author visit.

This year's book is New Kid by Jerry Craft. Learn more about our first Napa County Reads graphic novel!

Jerry Craft will visit Napa County on January 24, 2020 making presentations at several of our schools and live streaming into classrooms around the County. A community event is planned for the evening.

Napa Valley College Performing Arts Center
January 24, 2020
5:30 p.m. Author Reception in Lobby
6:00 – 7:30 p.m. Conversation with Author Jerry Craft
Adults $10, FREE for Students

This event is appropriate for adults and students. A portion of the proceeds will benefit the Napa County Reads program. Tickets will be sold at the door.

post_text:
Earlier this week NVUSD’s food program, NOSH - Napa’s Operative for School Food Health was invited to make lunch for Janet Napolitano, President of the University of California and her team of Vice Presidents at their monthly meeting. Napolitano is the first female president of UC; she is also a former Governor of Arizona and was Secretary of Homeland Security under President Barack Obama.
In 2014 Napolitano launched the UC Global Food Initiative which seeks to help schools teach healthy eating habits and provide nutritious, sustainable food to students. NOSH was selected to make lunch for the group to showcase this innovative thinking in action. The group was blown away with the quality of the food and excited to hear about what is happening in NVUSD with the use of local, fresh products.

post_text:
All NVUSD schools and offices will be open on Wednesday, November 20.

PG&E is implementing a Public Safety Power Shutdown (PSPS) tomorrow, November 20, starting at 7:00 am and lasting until 7:00 am on Thursday, November 21. The planned PSPS could affect 11,000 customers throughout the county of Napa, and we have confirmed that no NVUSD schools or school district sites fall within the power outage boundary.

We will continue to monitor the latest PSPS event by working cooperatively with the County of Napa Office of Emergency Services.

Should anything change, we will notify everyone as quickly as possible.

shared_text:
Napa Valley Education Foundation is at Napa Valley Unified School District.
November 15, 2019 at 11:12 PM · Napa, CA ·

Here is a fun #FlashbackFriday for you, dating back 95 years! We found this photo in one of our filing cabinets. It is a photo of the Napa High School Senior Bench, presented by the Class of 1924! We realized that the bench, the tree and even the building in the background are all still there, right outside our office windows at the Napa Valley Unified School District Ed. Center!
